Learning Management System (LMS)
Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
1. Introduction
The Learning Management System (LMS) is a web-based platform designed to manage, deliver, and track educational courses and training programs. This document defines the functional and non-functional requirements of the system and serves as a reference for development and evaluation.
2. Objectives
- Provide a scalable platform for online learning
- Allow instructors to create and manage courses
- Enable students to enroll and track progress
- Ensure secure access and role-based permissions
- Offer analytics and reporting for administrators
3. User Roles
Admin:
- Manage users and roles
- Manage categories and system settings

Instructor:
- Create and manage courses
- Upload lessons and content
- Manage course enrollments

Student:
- Enroll in courses
- Access content
- Track learning progress
4. Functional Requirements
4.1 Authentication & Authorization
- User registration and login
- JWT-based authentication
- Role-based access control (RBAC)
- Password hashing and secure storage
4.2 Course Management
- Create, update, delete courses
- Publish/unpublish courses
- Assign instructors
- Categorize courses
4.3 Enrollment Management
- Enroll/unenroll students
- Prevent duplicate enrollment
- Track enrollment status
4.4 Content Management
- Create sections and lessons
- Upload video, PDF, and text content
- Control lesson ordering
- Restrict access to enrolled users
4.5 Progress Tracking
- Track completed lessons
- Calculate course progress percentage
- Resume last accessed lesson
4.6 Reviews & Ratings
- Submit course reviews
- One review per student per course
- Rating calculation
5. Non-Functional Requirements
- Performance: Support concurrent users
- Security: Protect user data and content
- Scalability: Modular architecture
- Availability: High uptime
- Maintainability: Clean MVC structure
6. System Architecture
The system follows an MVC-based layered architecture:
- Controllers: API endpoints
- Services: Business logic
- Repositories: Data access
- Database: Relational database (SQL)
7. Assumptions & Constraints
- Internet access is required
- Users have basic digital literacy
- System is initially web-based only
8. Future Enhancements
- Subscription & payments
- Multi-tenant support
- Live classes & notifications
- Mobile application integration
- Certificate generation upon course completion
